Who would have thought.... the Pandemic would have aligned us together for me to join you in your journey of creating life changing history that will impact our communities for generations to come!

Marcus & Turquoise....I pray for us DAILY. There is a grand calling on us individually and collectively to build up our communities in such a way they will say our names profoundly on stages, award ceremonies, & history books while we're here on earth and after.

I pray God's covering & protection over us and our families and that He speaks to us Clearly the direction. I pray that he continues to keep us aligned and locked in with one another creating a strong force and foundation as we live in our Purpose!

Thank you @him500 & @her500_ for celebrating me in such a GRAND Way!!! Thank you for extending such an honor of holding the KEY to RECESSION PROOF to me that I do NOT take lightly or for granted!

Thank you my friend and sister Turquoise for hand picking me yourself!😄💪🏽 and Marcus for listening to her discernment and allowing me the capacity to lend you my gifts for the advancement of the organization and its members! I did not and do not take what you all have built any other way but serious!!

Thank you to our newly Inaugurated Arizona Chapter for celebrating my birthday on a day that you are to be celebrated on such a beautifully intentional way!

THANK you to all my hard azz working Executives for taking the time to send me personal messages, but most importantly... the dedication & commitment that YOU have serving in your Roles so graciously! I will ALWAYS be an Advocate on your behalf because you DESERVE IT!

🍷WELP.... they done gave the RIGHT one the Key.... this just my warm up lap!!!!! 

2023 Let's Be Ouuuut!!!

EYL powered by Recession Proof.... let's Go make History!!!💪🏽💪🏽💪🏽💯💯💯

LET'S GO!!

😎The People's Secret Weapon!😎

Cheers 🍷,
Syndy B.

12 YEARS BAE!!!!! 🎉🎉 I RECALL the day when I KNEW... My Honey Bun loved our family....TRULY.... to the DEPTHS! 

We were fresh in our new relationship. I was a Licensed Insurance Rep at that time and all my clientele took place all the way in the WestEnd Area Atlanta and we lived on the WAY North and we only had one car at the time and Uber was not around. 

He had to work that late morning rather than the typical afternoon after I got home from work. That man told me to take the car that early morning and when it was time for his work, he proceeded to walk 10 miles to work that day and work a full 8 hour Day! He never complained and NEVER talks about it! But it's just ONE of many examples of why.....Y'all Already KNOW!!! 

ION Play about my Honey Bun!🤨💪🏽🤗 

Every battle we armored up and faced together...often in silence.... just me and him handling our ish to reestablish, establish, & build ourselves to a bigger and better place for us and our children. 

I don't want to do life with ANYONE else my love. You IT...DAS IT...& I LOVE YOU!! Cheers to 12×12 More Years of Beautiful Memories together! 

🎉🎉HAPPY ANNIVERSARY HONEY BUN @coachryanbuchanan ! 🎉🎉

Your Forever #1 Rider "Light Skin"💋
Syndy B.

My Honey Bun has been a bit concerned about this Woman in his life lately. But, he knows flowers will boost my energy any day! 

While I wait to have another meeting tonight, these flowers were intentional and why I just love this man of mine!

***transparent moment***

Health wise, I'm very low energy and I haven't been feeling my greatest for about 4-5 months now (I know... you would never know). 

I'm pretty sure my blood pressure is low in the midst of it all. I know I need to do better with my eating (I basically need to eat more), definitely need to cut my salt intake, and increase my Vitamins, especially the way that I go go go all the time!

I say all that to say.... as a Woman in her 40s, who intends to leave a legacy of historical progressive movements before I leave this earth, I promise myself to be more intentional about taking care of my internal self as I learn how my body likes to operate in this new age of life. 💞FAMILY💞

I come from a family that's VERY tight. We are with each other through the good & the not so great. We are loyal, we are united, & funny as HELL!😄

And that's exactly how we roll with people we call family, coz that's how we get down, coz that's how we were raised!

I go home for restoration and to nurture my soul and spirit.

First Pic is my AMAZING Mommy & Daddy, One of my many handsome nephews, my 1st born nephew (my big baby love!🤗), & his wife my niece. 

Then, you see a pic of the BADDEST women walking this earth!!! My Aunties!!!! I learned some of the best life secrets from them!! And another Auntie pic that includes my Cuz the Bride, has my GREAT Aunt who is about to turn 90!!

Then, a big group of my Cousins!!! Man!!! My cousins are like siblings! We grew up together...a big Ole crew of us (this is my Daddy's side.... he's 1 of 7 children!)

That last pic.... me and 2 of my Cousins and one of my Aunts (Aunt Myrna took the pic) went to Brunch in Maryland before I headed back home and was there for 7 hours!! CTFU!!!!!😆😆😆

This is why my whole essence is so strong....I come from strong roots!

Needless to say, after 4 days of being home.... my cup is full and runneth over!!!

It's the Robinsons For Me!!!

LOVE YOU FAMILY!!! You made me!!!

Happy Women's History Month!!!

Your Favorite Relationship Coach, 
Syndy B.💋

A Father's Love is UNMATCHED!!!!

Growing up, the men in my life... starting with my Daddy, on to my Uncles, Cousins, My Daddy's Friends, & the Men in my community.... we as women felt PROTECTED!!!!

There was a level of responsibility that men had for women that did not have to be spoken... it was understood.

I'm so THANKFUL that my Daddy loved on us so hard! We could not even go to bed all the way through high school without coming to give big hugs goodnight! And even the very FEW times he spanked us.... we had to give him a hug after🫣😄 (low-key was one of the best lessons in that discipline does not have to mean lack of love).

My Daddy loving on me is the SAME love I see and receive from my Honey Bun Hubby..... and that will be passed on to our children. They will NOT be confused on what love should look and feel like!

And I've been loved on so much by my family and friends... and if you REALLY Know me.... Family is EVERYTHING to me... and my close friends are also like family to me!

Love you Daddy... your legacy and life lives on through us!

****TRUE INTERESTING STORY****

This picture was taken on May 17, 2014.... just 14 Days after celebrating my son's 4th Birthday....

.... AND ONLY 3 DAYS AFTER... one of my clients, where I had a SIX FIGURE Retainer.... BOUNCED!!!

... along with over 15 other contractors' invoices and 3 Staffed Employees PAYROLL checks!!!!

I experienced and was able to rebuild after the Real Estate market crash... but I had never experienced a multi-million dollar revenued business not carry through on their obligations!!! And worse!!! Did not tell anyone!

Imagine... OVERNIGHT....a Six Figure income vanishing from your household!!!

My kids were in private school at that time. As a contractor...I was not able to go seek unemployment or file a suit with the Department of Labor. I had to suck it up!

BUT!!! Having my business experience, knowing how to pivot in business, having multiple professional licensing including my License in Life & Health, & knowing how to leverage Corporate & Government money...our kids remained in Private School until we moved them 3 years later to Public School, we were able to purchase our home in 2016, and keep on trucking! Not saying it wasn't a struggle... but we pulled through and were able to rebuild!

The point..... you better have your eggs in more than one basket!!! Especially if you're in Corporate America... but even as a Business Owner with clients!

I only trust in my OWN efforts and that God will do the rest!

At an age I don't remember, because I was a baby, my Biological  Mother, who was married to my dad at the time...

...Decided to up and ABANDON Myself, My Big Sis, & My Dad!!

Yep! There are mothers out there who abandon their children, too! I searched for her and found her in my early 20s... but that's not the point of this story... maybe another "Storytime!"

BUT! My dad... the GREATEST of all Dads was left to raise his two daughters on his own (with the help of family of course) until he met my AMAZING Mommy who he married when I was about 5 or 6! (One quick way to get me heated is call her my Stepmom😤....I digressed!)

The 2nd slide is the home he raised us in...a 2 Bedroom 1 Bath 725 Sq.Ft. Home Honey!!!!

Miss Edna across the street watched all the neighborhood kids and many of us would walk up the street with our $1 or $2 to the 7-11 on the corner to get candy necklaces, jolly ranchers, & hot pickles 😄

***PRENUP....OR NO PRENUP??!***

And don't brag that you "DON'T" have a prenup...b/c that ain't cute either!!

None of it's "fun"... but at the end of the day.... you need a marriage LICENSE for a reason! It's BUSINESS!

Now... whether or not you decide to have a prenuptial or not is on you.

BUT, I'll say this... having been married before with NO prenup....I handled my business like a real boss should!

We were in the middle of opening a clinic.  I leveraged my money to rebuild his credit so we could get a small business loan ($750K was approved). We were set for payroll for a year, he had the relationships on deck, and build out started.

Into it... we became separated. I still networked with the wives of the doctors who were going to send us patients, even showed up to a baby shower of one of the doctors because he had to be out of town...all while I was living separated. 

Even showed my azz to the ribbon cutting as a united front!!!

All for him to try to fight me from not having my equity in the business!😩

It would have cost me major in legal fees to win that case than I could afford on my own.

So... for my sanity...I walked away... and in the middle of hearings... told the Judge I wanted nothing(I do not recommend... fight for your ish!!! But...I was about 25 at that time... no one in my circle had even been married but maybe 1).

3 or 4 clinics later....well... you get my point!

Not having a prenup can be just as bad!

Point of this.... happily married or not.... HAVE👏🏽 YOUR👏🏽 OWN👏🏽 SHIT👏🏽!!!!! (You know I'm serious if I cuss!)

👀If I ruffled your feathers, put a knot in your stomach, or made you uncomfortable...or even pissed!

STORY & MESSAGE TIME!

In 2005/2006-ish...I made my 1st Six Figures at the age of 23/24.

It's not the Six Figures I want you to take note of. (I hate ending sentences with a preposition 😅)

My motivation at that time was, I did NOT want to go back to a 9-5! 

I left my stable job as a manager at a well-known bank to become a Loan Officer, and after a few months with a company, I went out on my own under a Broker. 

After 3 or 4 months of ZERO closings...I went into "MAKE THIS SH* HAPPEN!!" Mode!

For 2 Months or so, I wore the SAME type of black pants & black sweater to my office everyday that people thought I was wearing the actual same outfit. 😄

I didn't want to spend time thinking about what I was going to wear every day!

I was on a mission! I wanted to just get up and go as quickly and as early as possible to meet my deadline of 6 months of making this thing happen!

I did not know at that time that some of our legends such as Albert Einstein, Mark Zuckerberg, &  Steve Jobs wore their signature plain wardrobe to take away one less decision everyday as decision fatigue is a real thing!

TAKEAWAYS:

1. Don't GAF what everyone else is doing... do what YOU gotta do to reach your goals!

2. Be decisive & commit to the journey!

3. STOP making excuses... get it done! Yes.... life can be real rough and throw rocks on your pathway to throw you off course... but if you can just keep going... you'll get through it!

4. Keep Learning Who YOU are so opportunities not meant for you don't become distractions. The more you succeed, the more opportunities come your way. Although you want to be open for opportunities, you must KNOW your lane!!

⭕️ Not only did it take WORK to get to the place I'm at... I'm GRATEFUL for my blessings!!! 

And how dare I not place light on them and show how Thankful I am at a Second chance in life!

⭕️ IYKYK.... To be a Woman, Wife, & Mom in a Male Dominated Space... it's ROOOOOOUUUUUGH!!!!!!! 

😊I smile through it because I'm built for it... but trust and believe....

I deal with and manage my Stress, Anxiety, & Schedule EVERY DAY in this Space I've been in for a while with intention, purpose, & care!!

⭕️ But....I could not do it without my Rocks!!!

💫 My Honey Bun...a Business Management Major, a Masters Degree in Sports Psychology, a Retired Coach, a Business Owner, & also a Mental Health Service Worker on Many Nights at a Mental Health Facility.... With ALL of that... He STEPS UP & IN for me during the Busy season Times!! 

And instead of making me (using that word... but no one can make you feel something) feel guilty... we lock in and put in the Winning Plays!!

💫 My Girls...My Sisters... who step in to watch the Babies for us when I'm gone and The Honey Bun has to work at night, or simply check in to see what's needed, and my BIGGEST Cheerleaders!! I could not do it in stride without them!

SUPPORT is essential!! Personally & Professionally!!!

So being on this 9 City Legacy Tour with CEO & Mentor Marcus @him500 Barney to be the support his Mentees need is WORTH EVERY sacrifice!!

Speaking of Circles... @alix_goodenergy will be joining us in Houston tomorrow!! Because... it's the ⭕️ !!💪🏽💪🏽

See You Tomorrow Houston!!!
